articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Dawoud Abu Alkas
articles.description: Health officials said an Israeli airstrike killed five people in a house in the Nuseirat camp in central Gaza, while another airstrike killed four others in Jabalia in the northern edge of the enclave.
articles.title: Israeli strikes kill nine people in Gaza, mediators strive for a truce deal

articles.author: Hyonhee Shin
articles.description: Thousands braved heavy snow in Seoul on Sunday to rally for and against arresting impeached President Yoon Suk Yeol, as South Korea's political crisis appeared headed toward another high-stakes confrontation.
articles.title: South Korea protesters rally for, against Yoon arrest as deadline looms

articles.author: Mark Trevelyan
articles.description: Ukrainian forces have launched a major new attack in Russia's western Kursk region, Russian military bloggers reported on Sunday.
articles.title: Russian war bloggers report new Ukrainian attack in Kursk region

articles.author: Francois Murphy
articles.description: The leadership of Austria's ruling conservatives held a crisis meeting on Sunday to pick a successor to Chancellor Karl Nehammer, who announced his resignation on Saturday as attempts to form a coalition government without the far right fell apart.
articles.title: Austrian conservatives hold crisis meeting after chancellor quits

articles.author: William Schomberg
articles.description: It was an abrupt withdrawal of support.
articles.title: Musk turns on UK's Farage and says he should quit as Reform party leader

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Convoys of farmers set off on Sunday to try to block roads around Paris in protest against what they say is unfair competition from overseas and excessive regulation.
articles.title: Farmers' convoys head for Paris to restart protest movement

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Thousands of Montenegrins gathered in the town of Cetinje on Sunday to commemorate the 12 victims of a mass shooting last week, with many accusing police of not having done enough to stop the gunman's rampage.
articles.title: Anger and tears as Montenegro town commemorates mass shooting victims

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Ecuador's former Vice President Jorge Glas has been evacuated from prison after an attempt on his life, his lawyer said on Sunday, blaming the government for the situation.
articles.title: Ecuador's ex-VP Glas evacuated from prison after attempted killing, lawyer says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Syrian Foreign Minister Asaad Hassan al-Shibani, appointed by the country's new rulers, arrived in Doha on Sunday to meet Qatar's Prime Minister Sheikh Mohammed bin Abdulrahman Al Thani, a Qatari official told Reuters.
articles.title: Syrian foreign minister in Doha to meet Qatar's prime minister

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Turkish President Tayyip Erdogan said on Sunday that Syria's new leadership is determined to root out separatists there, as Ankara said its military had "neutralised" 32 members of the outlawed Kurdistan Workers Party, or PKK, in the country.
articles.title: Erdogan expects support from Syria in Turkey's battle with PKK
